<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4563758>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 9. Tanystylum occidentale, UANL-FCB-PYCNO-0064, male: A, proboscis, frontal view; B, cephalic segment, dorsal view; C, palp and chelifore; D, ocular tubercle, lateral view; E, complete specimen; F, third leg, dorsal view; G, cement gland; H, tibia 2, tarsus, propodus, and claws of third leg; I, ovigers, ventral view; J, oviger, enlarged; K, abdomen, dorsal view; L, abdomen, lateral view. Scale bars: E = 1 mm; F, I–J = 0.5 mm; B, H = 0.2 mm; C–D, G, K–L = 0.1 mm; A = 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4563758/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4563740>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Area of study showing the nine marine docks located along the peninsular coast of the Gulf of California, Mexico. 1 = Cabo San Lucas; 2 = Puerto Los Cabos; 3 = FONATUR-Fidepaz; 4 = La Paz; 5 = Fiscal Pier, 6 = Palmira, 7 = Cantamar; 8 = Puerto Escondido (located about 50 km south of Loreto), and 9 = FONATUR-Santa Rosalía, Baja California Sur, Mexico. A magnification of the map shown marine docks 3–7 located at Bahía de La Paz." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4563740/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4563756>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 8. Tanystylum occidentale, UANL-FCB-PYCNO-0064, male:A, trunk, dorsal view; B, trunk, lateral view; C, palp; D, third leg; E, propodus; F, female oviger; G) male oviger. Scale bars: A–B, D = 0.5 mm; E = 0.3 mm; C, F–G = 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4563756/files/figure.png" .

